  <div class="note">
  <h3> Note from the artist:</h3>
  <p>Beginning with fine arts painting I have had a font with pasting colors on a white canvas in front of me. Riding the train to Waterloo with my mother, venturing to the art museums that I could barely tour because of my short 12-year-old legs, remain vivid as some of my favorite childhood memories. Those echoing galleries were too large to explore completely, but each visit made me eager to see more. The grand canvases of the Renaissance enveloped me and I suddenly felt alone in the museum, enjoying the beauty. The feelings led me to pursue art, starting with little doodles then moving to a full-sized canvas, painting to express my fantasies. Art gave me freedomâ€”not just in what I could create, but in how I could connect ideas. Through art, I could capture the abstract possibilities hidden within each element I rendered. I love to find the essence of a subject and weave different media together into a single yarn, crafting pieces of art that highlight the simplicity and charm of one component, while integrating others to form more intricate and expressive ideas.</p>
  </div>
